article.headline: St. Francis, NY 82, Fairleigh Dickinson 72
article.story: NEW YORK -- Ricky Cadell scored 26 points to lead St. Francis, N.Y. to an 82-72 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday. Stefan Perunicic had four 3-pointers and scored 16 points for the Terriers (9-16, 7-8 Northeast Conference), while Nigel Byam had 14. Sean Baptiste had 22 points to lead the Knights (7-19, 6-9), while Alvin Mofunanya had 15 and 12 rebounds and Terence Grier added 12 points. Baptiste's 3-pointer with 4:19 to play tied the game at 63, but Cadell scored five points in a 7-0 run that gave the Terriers a 70-63 lead with 48 seconds to go. Cadell, who leads the team in scoring with a 13.7 average, was 8-of-14 from the field and 8-of-11 from the free throw line.
